For primesieve-4.3

+ Document (ChangeLog) new std::vector<T> functionality.
+ Document (ChangeLog) new stop_primesieve exception class.
+ Document (ChangeLog) improved pre-sieving.
+ Rewrite some of the source code examples e.g. using the new
  std::vector<T> functionality and stop_primesieve.h.
+ Update doc/Examples, doc/FAQ, doc/API.
+ Silence MSVC /W4 warnings.
+ Add version 1.0 to scripts/install_primesieve.sh

---------------------------------------------------

1. Make ParallelPrimeSieve exception safe and implement cancellation.

   This requires OpenMP 4.0 which will be released in the coming
   months. More precisely I plan the following design: if an exception
   is caught in one thread this thread cancels all other threads using
   the new `#pragma omp cancel' clause from OpenMP 4.0 (and then
   probably rethrow the exception).
